//
// The QuantaLang Package Manager (quanta) handles dependency management,
// building, testing, and publishing of QuantaLang packages.
//
// Features:
// - Manifest parsing (quanta.toml)
// - Semantic versioning with version requirements
// - Lock file generation for reproducible builds
// - PubGrub-inspired dependency resolution
// - Registry integration with sparse index protocol
// - Workspace support
// - Feature unification
//
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

//! # QuantaLang Package Manager
//!
//! This crate provides package management functionality for QuantaLang projects.
//!
//! ## Quick Start
//!
//! ```bash
//! # Create a new package
//! quanta new my-project
//! cd my-project
//!
//! # Add a dependency
//! quanta add serde --features derive
//!
//! # Build the project
//! quanta build --release
//!
//! # Run tests
//! quanta test
//! ```
//!
//! ## Manifest Format (quanta.toml)
//!
//! ```toml
//! [package]
//! name = "my-project"
//! version = "0.1.0"
//! edition = "2025"
//! authors = ["Your Name <you@example.com>"]
//! description = "A sample QuantaLang project"
//! license = "MIT"
//!
//! [dependencies]
//! serde = { version = "1.0", features = ["derive"] }
//! tokio = { version = "1.0", features = ["full"] }
//!
//! [dev-dependencies]
//! pretty_assertions = "1.0"
//!
//! [features]
//! default = ["std"]
//! std = []
//! ```
//!
//! ## Modules
//!
//! - [`manifest`] - Manifest file parsing and serialization
//! - [`version`] - Semantic versioning implementation
//! - [`lockfile`] - Lock file management
//! - [`resolver`] - Dependency resolution algorithm
//! - [`registry`] - Package registry client
//! - [`cli`] - Command-line interface

